History

Founded by Patti Webster in 1991, W&W has a sincere commitment to excellence. From representation of young artists to the most famous brands, the W&W company motto is âa good name is rather to be chosen than riches.â For 25 years, W&W has maintained its stellar reputation for producing and executing public relation campaigns and special events that are well managed, heavily attended and that receive valuable exposure via print, radio, television and digital media.

W&W is proud of its diverse group of clientele, past and present, including Janet Jackson, Alicia Keys, Usher, Kelly Rowland, Steve Harvey, Patti LaBelle, Dwight Howard, Chris Paul, Holly Robinson Peete, Ludacris, Bow Wow, Mary Mary, KEM, So So Def Recordings, eOne Music, Jermaine Dupri, Rasheed Wallace, Crown Royal, The Estate of Otis Redding, The Steve & Marjory Harvey Foundation, The Rasheed A. Wallace Foundation, The HollyRod Foundation, the Chris Paul Family Foundation, The Neighborhood Awards and others. Over the years, W&W has developed strong relationships with mainstream and niche media organizations.
